en:
Businesses located outside the Communauté métropolitaine de Montréal providing private health care as well as body and beauty care services may resume their activities. This reopening applies to:
*   oral care clinics and dental centres (all dental care);
*   businesses in the therapeutic care sector (clinics in the fields of physiotherapy, osteopathy, occupational therapy, chiropractic, massage therapy, psychology, optometry, acupuncture, naturopathy, homeopathy, career guidance, social work, marriage and family therapy, sexology and other forms of therapy, nutrition, speech therapy and audiology, podiatry, other forms of alternative medicine, etc.);
*   pet grooming;
*   businesses in the personal care and beauty sector (hair stylists, barbers, beauty centres, manicure and pedicure salons, hair removal, skin care, tattooing, piercing, etc.).
For the territories of the Communauté métropolitaine de Montréal and the MRC de Joliette, only dental care, therapeutic care and pet grooming may resume their activities since June 1. Businesses in the personal- and beauty-care sector can resume their activities starting from June 15, 2020 in both territories.
